# Suno

## Suno v4 Text-to-Song

- **owner**: suno-ai
- **id**: chirp-v4
- **tier**: powerful

### Description

Suno v4 is an AUDIO text-to-song model that generates complete musical compositions with vocals,
instrumentation, and production from a text prompt or lyrics. The leading model for AI-generated
songs across all genres — essential for temp tracks, theme song prototyping, mood reels, and
content that needs licensed-free original music with singing.

### Best Practices

- Provide both a style descriptor and explicit lyrics for best control: use `[Verse]`, `[Chorus]`,
  `[Bridge]` structural tags in the lyrics field to guide song architecture.
- Style prompt should specify genre + sub-genre + instrumentation + mood + era + vocal style
  ("indie folk, fingerpicked acoustic guitar, breathy female vocal, melancholic, early 2000s").
- Generate multiple seeds and pick the strongest take; vocal phrasing varies significantly between
  runs. Use the extend/continue feature to build longer compositions from a strong 30-second seed.

## Suno v4 Instrumental

- **owner**: suno-ai
- **id**: chirp-v4-instrumental
- **tier**: balanced

### Description

Suno v4 Instrumental is an AUDIO text-to-music model generating full instrumental compositions
without vocals — ideal for background scoring, temp tracks, transition music, title sequences,
and any use case where vocals would compete with dialogue or narration.

### Best Practices

- Specify instrumentation explicitly rather than just genre: "orchestral strings, muted trumpet,
  brushed snare, upright bass, jazz club atmosphere, slow burn tension."
- Include tempo/BPM hints and dynamic arc cues ("builds from sparse intro to full ensemble at
  0:30") for better structural control.
- Generate 4–6 candidates per prompt and curate; loop-friendly prompts ("seamless, 4/4, no
  dramatic ending") help for background use.
